## ğŸš« Anti-Patterns to Avoid

### Architecture Anti-Patterns
- âŒ **Monolithic components**: Don't create components with too many responsibilities
- âŒ **Deep nesting**: Avoid deeply nested component hierarchies
- âŒ **Global state abuse**: Don't put everything in global state
- âŒ **Prop drilling**: Use context or state management instead

### Code Quality Anti-Patterns
- âŒ **Any types**: Avoid using `any` - use proper typing
- âŒ **Inline styles**: Use Tailwind classes instead
- âŒ **Hardcoded values**: Use constants and environment variables
- âŒ **Console logs**: Remove console.log statements in production

### Performance Anti-Patterns
- âŒ **Unnecessary re-renders**: Avoid creating objects/functions in render
- âŒ **Large bundles**: Don't import entire libraries when you only need specific functions
- âŒ **Memory leaks**: Clean up event listeners and subscriptions

